HEADWORD: Chondropterygii
<hw>Chon*drop`te*ryg"i*i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ cartilage + <?/, <?/, wing, fin.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of fishes, characterized by
cartilaginous fins and skeleton. It includes both ganoids (sturgeons,
etc.) and selachians (sharks), but is now often restricted to the
latter.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Chondropterygia</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

